msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/solid_mechanics.rst:49
#: b5e32cd90e4940fab9786c5f0d539ef8
msgid "Hyperelastic Beam (Neo-Hookean)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/solid_mechanics.rst:51
#: da90229e20384ca696edf9b4ca802efb
msgid "Hyperelastic Rubber Beam under Torsion"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/solid_mechanics.rst:58
#: 3d43a6a88d9342f3a920ad2fa7512c28
msgid ""
"Hyperelasticity models large deformations where the stress-strain "
"relationship is nonlinear. The Neo-Hookean model is a fundamental "
"hyperelastic constitutive law."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/solid_mechanics.rst:61
#: 666ba677c049450ca7c10e25c22135fe
msgid "The deformation gradient is defined as:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/solid_mechanics.rst:63
#: fa5bc33156d840f5aebde6e520d8a805
#, python-brace-format
msgid "\\mathbf{F} = \\mathbf{I} + \\nabla \\mathbf{u}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/solid_mechanics.rst:67
#: 72860610222b41e6bde5cd4e55d88d9b
msgid ""
"The strain energy density function for compressible Neo-Hookean material "
"is:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/solid_mechanics.rst:69
#: 77f214168b0c446bb533d854e121afe4
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"\\Psi = \\frac{\\mu}{2}(I_1 - 3) - \\mu \\ln J + \\frac{\\lambda}{2}(\\ln"
" J)^2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/solid_mechanics.rst:73
#: ../../source/examples/solid_mechanics.rst:115
#: de396908f9ca43458bc9e9578d215c87 e0dd1dad896e4483a3bb4065da43c997
msgid "where:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/solid_mechanics.rst:75
#: 3dc78a372b3549669d959b8aac597916
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
":math:`I_1 = \\text{tr}(\\mathbf{F}^T \\mathbf{F})` is the first "
"invariant of the right Cauchy-Green tensor"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/solid_mechanics.rst:76
#: 9960b0304e894fe29617b4b852a78782
#, python-brace-format
msgid ":math:`J = \\det(\\mathbf{F})` is the Jacobian (volume ratio)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/solid_mechanics.rst:77
#: f5f30477d2764d4ea512d037cff6c74d
msgid ":math:`\\mu, \\lambda` are Lamé parameters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/solid_mechanics.rst:79
#: 40825828b8c044888c675a1e1e5bb6e9
msgid "The total potential energy is minimized:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/solid_mechanics.rst:81
#: a3e1b0b7918b48f8a4efe0263119128f
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"\\Pi(\\mathbf{u}) = \\int_\\Omega \\Psi(\\mathbf{F}) \\, dV - "
"\\int_\\Omega \\mathbf{f} \\cdot \\mathbf{u} \\, dV"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/solid_mechanics.rst:92
#: 00be6f47ded849cd9afea081ebde4396
msgid "3D Plasticity (J2 Flow Theory)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/solid_mechanics.rst:94
#: c4041b309a09401f96d8f6f1f32325bf
msgid "<div style=\"text-align: center;\">"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/solid_mechanics.rst:103
#: 48fef41d46434983a9cb65a8094ac616
msgid "</div>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/solid_mechanics.rst:107
#: 05c6caa3fa9a45f4a9d10534a72bce91
msgid ""
"J2 plasticity (von Mises plasticity) is the most common model for metal "
"plasticity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/solid_mechanics.rst:109
#: 281f5d9fe6fd46c584876dab20607bab
msgid "The yield function is:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/solid_mechanics.rst:111
#: 5702e19ef49c46aea9efc9add651f12d
msgid ""
"f(\\boldsymbol{\\sigma}, \\alpha) = \\sqrt{\\frac{3}{2} \\mathbf{s} : "
"\\mathbf{s}} - (\\sigma_y + H \\alpha) = 0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/solid_mechanics.rst:117
#: 9f68014d4d354cd489e00ab7835581a7
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
":math:`\\mathbf{s} = \\boldsymbol{\\sigma} - "
"\\frac{1}{3}\\text{tr}(\\boldsymbol{\\sigma})\\mathbf{I}` is the "
"deviatoric stress"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/solid_mechanics.rst:118
#: ffaf42acb59148ecb5d4e41d112e33b3
msgid ":math:`\\sigma_y` is the initial yield stress"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/solid_mechanics.rst:119
#: db9b3c1c9fad456f9456b947409184a0
msgid ":math:`H` is the hardening modulus"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/solid_mechanics.rst:120
#: 4da3a64312c0449badc7c59dd9456cad
msgid ":math:`\\alpha` is the equivalent plastic strain (internal variable)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/solid_mechanics.rst:122
#: 46398e25788146448d3271c7f2a40753
msgid "The plastic strain evolution follows the associative flow rule:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/solid_mechanics.rst:124
#: ec51785748b74f968fc1335a08d07340
msgid ""
"\\dot{\\boldsymbol{\\varepsilon}}^p = \\dot{\\gamma} \\frac{\\partial "
"f}{\\partial \\boldsymbol{\\sigma}} = \\dot{\\gamma} \\sqrt{\\frac{3}{2}}"
" \\frac{\\mathbf{s}}{||\\mathbf{s}||}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/solid_mechanics.rst:128
#: 87bbf71a943848c0a42ddf1d343d0777
msgid ""
"The simulation demonstrates loading and unloading cycles, showing the "
"characteristic hysteresis loop of elasto-plastic materials."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/solid_mechanics.rst:138
#: 982c8d9ac35543a18d94a78d011d8d0c
msgid "Hertzian Contact (Circle on Block)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/solid_mechanics.rst:140
#: bcb680167f334ead9374312bb8114e8b
msgid "Hertzian Contact Stress Distribution"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/solid_mechanics.rst:147
#: 40d58742e5f5407ba6ae92ea2092e560
msgid ""
"The Hertzian contact stress problem describes the localized stresses that"
" develop as two curved surfaces come in contact and deform slightly under"
" the imposed loads. This example simulates a circular indenter (Slave) "
"pressed against a flat rectangular block (Master)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/solid_mechanics.rst:149
#: 8516a721fe5c49a797606759051882f1
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"The contact condition is enforced using the **Point-to-Segment** penalty "
"method. For every slave node :math:`\\mathbf{x}_s` on the indenter "
"surface, we find the closest point :math:`\\mathbf{x}_c` on the master "
"surface segments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/solid_mechanics.rst:151
#: 7d3a097eed504dcea8905af0abcc15e4
msgid "The gap function is defined as:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/solid_mechanics.rst:153
#: 5d237f2290d04f89bb2f4cfa73de3b80
#, python-brace-format
msgid "g = (\\mathbf{x}_s - \\mathbf{x}_c) \\cdot \\mathbf{n}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/solid_mechanics.rst:157
#: 2673be3722144e1ca9159c38844817ba
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"where :math:`\\mathbf{n}` is the normal vector of the master segment. The"
" penalty energy is:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/solid_mechanics.rst:159
#: 9fed3ca7ed924a03b324732bfdca2f02
msgid "E_{\\text{contact}} = \\frac{1}{2} k_p \\sum_{g < 0} g^2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/solid_mechanics.rst:163
#: add9390bcfa1419da131ef13b2cead07
msgid "where :math:`k_p` is a large penalty parameter to enforce non-penetration."
msgstr ""

